			        <a href='http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Referendum' target='_blank'> referendums</a><%= info_help('info_referendum') %>.
			        This means that people vote directly on law proposals and propose new laws.</br></br>
			        			
			
			In addition, <a href='http://www.democratie-directe.be' target='_blank'>we</a> want to bring so-called <a href='http://www.participedia.net/wiki/Liquid_Democracy' target='_blank'>liquid democracy</a>.</br>
			        This allows voters to select a delegate who will vote for them when they want to. But the crucial point is that voters can change their delegate, 
			        or take their vote back at anytime! Also, anyone can become a delegate, including you...</br></br>
			
			
